Dialogue: 1,0:02:12.44,0:02:21.45,EP Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(2100,0)\be1}One-Night Bridge
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.84,0:02:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Gee, what a nice bridge...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.96,0:02:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Guess I'll have to cross.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.54,0:02:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, it's already about to give way!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.63,0:02:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, how nerve-wracking.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.50,0:02:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you from these parts?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.95,0:03:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.88,0:03:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,This bridge is on its last legs!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.25,0:03:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But I've to cross this bridge on my way back.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.09,0:03:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.85,0:03:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,, I'll do something about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.89,0:03:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,How long will you be around?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.58,0:03:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Frankly, I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.77,0:03:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know the sender of this letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.65,0:03:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.23,0:03:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for coming such a long way.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.49,0:03:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.90,0:03:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my daughter, Hana.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.53,0:03:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Around three years ago, she fell off that \Nvine bridge and into the ravine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.30,0:03:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,She survived, but ever since then...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.43,0:03:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All she does is sit in the sun in a daze like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.88,0:03:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I've taken her around to many doctors,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.97,0:04:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,but since there's no sign that she hit her head, we still don't know the cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.44,0:04:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.90,0:04:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... How's Hana?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.03,0:04:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you're friends?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.50,0:04:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Hana is that way because of... me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.21,0:04:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, I want you to help her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.19,0:04:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Take me the bottom of the ravine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.82,0:04:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Also... I want you to tell me how she fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.40,0:04:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,C'mon... stop crying...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.67,0:05:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't turn down a marriage offer from the head family...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.90,0:05:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah... if you refuse, they'll probably \Nstop helping our village, I guess...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.19,0:05:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Well... not that you could refuse, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.06,0:05:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall we run away?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.77,0:05:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But... If we did such a thing,\N our families would be ostracized.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.97,0:05:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,My parents would understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.94,0:05:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And if your parents really want you to be happy, they'd be able to bear it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.13,0:05:42.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If we stay here, we can't live the way we want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.93,0:05:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's leave the valley and cross the \Nmountains to a wide-open, bright land!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.93,0:05:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do it, Hana!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.31,0:06:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Careful, it's bit weak there...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.61,0:06:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Zen...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.22,0:06:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.67,0:06:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't do it...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.60,0:06:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't right for just the two of us to become happy...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.57,0:06:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Hana...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.33,0:06:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I can put up with it...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.02,0:06:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Zen... you'll always still love me, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.69,0:06:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll always love you, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.29,0:06:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if I've to smother my true heart once I'm there...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.92,0:06:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want it to be like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.47,0:06:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, let's cross the bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.68,0:06:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Hana!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.82,0:07:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Hana!!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.89,0:07:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you found her?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.60,0:07:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.84,0:07:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,She fell from a height she couldn't\N possibly have survived...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.25,0:07:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But Hana came back, walking on her own two feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.48,0:07:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But... she came back a shell of her former self.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.96,0:08:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone lamented that she became a {\i1}tani-modori.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.35,0:08:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Tani-modori?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.29,0:08:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They say people like that appear \Nin this ravine once in a great while.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.34,0:08:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They fall into the ravine...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.33,0:08:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and luckily come back, but without their souls.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.50,0:08:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Then they die on the night when \Nthe "One-Night Bridge" spans.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.02,0:08:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's probably just a legend, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.41,0:08:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,One-Night Bridge?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.92,0:08:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people say they've seen a bridge \Nthat spans the ravine for just one night.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.93,0:08:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That was quite a long time ago, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.01,0:08:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.72,0:08:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.09,0:08:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like they're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.09,0:08:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What are?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.65,0:08:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The same things that have taken over Hana.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.80,0:08:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Hana... has been taken over?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.17,0:08:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, by vine-shaped mushi called {\i1}Nise-kazura.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.81,0:08:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't see anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.53,0:09:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They're usually hard to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.03,0:09:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They're awfully weak for Nise-kazura.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.66,0:09:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}If I pull in the opposite direction, they're strong...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.98,0:09:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Just like the Nise-kazura I read about.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.75,0:09:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The sunlight is no longer shining through?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.41,0:09:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They're gathering toward the remaining sunlight...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.39,0:09:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}So this area is sorely lacking sunlight?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.95,0:09:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So how'd it go? Learn anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.75,0:10:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,This'll be hard for you to accept...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.25,0:10:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.85,0:10:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The {\i1}tani-modori{\i0} and the One-Night Bridge are probably not just legends...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.55,0:10:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Both can be explained by {\i1}Nise-kazura.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.52,0:10:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Normally, {\i1}Nise-kazura{\i0} live in the treetops.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.30,0:10:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But the {\i1}Nise-kazura{\i0} in this ravine are probably trying to get out by taking over the bodies of creatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.97,0:10:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because they need more sunlight,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.44,0:10:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,but they lack the strength to climb out of the ravine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.08,0:10:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They dwell in the bodies of creatures to get more sunlight and build their strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.71,0:10:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Each time enough of them have done so,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.46,0:10:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,they leave their hosts and form groups\N to get across the ravine...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.74,0:10:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,, and move to a better location...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.40,0:10:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what the One-Night Bridge probably is.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.90,0:11:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I've heard before...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.29,0:11:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,1769)}that there's a ravine where mushi cross over once every 20 years or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.07,0:11:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Then... why do the {\i1}tani-modori{\i0} \Nhave to die when that happens?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.81,0:11:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If those mushi things leave, \Nwon't they return to normal?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.16,0:11:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I explored the bottom of the ravine, \Nand I found no animal bones.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.53,0:11:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a high likelihood that the {\i1}Nise-kazura{\i0} are living in dead bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.61,0:11:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's so, even if they leave, \Nonly a dead body would be left.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.42,0:11:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No... Then you mean Hana will eventually be?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.13,0:11:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This {\i1}is{\i0} the year!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.84,0:11:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard the One-Night Bridge was seen on the year of my grandpa's birth.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.47,0:12:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Grandpa is 60 this year!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.06,0:12:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't there any way to delay it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.75,0:12:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.99,0:12:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not asking you to bring her back to the way she was.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.26,0:12:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want her to stay alive just a little bit longer...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.31,0:12:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So please...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.83,0:12:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.10,0:12:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.13,0:12:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm afraid that keeping her like this is \Nthe best way to extend her life...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.77,0:12:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You can remove the mushi, can't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.76,0:12:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes... But if I did, in all probability, she'd die instantly...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.57,0:12:43.82,Alt,,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.69,0:12:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think she's happy living like this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.88,0:12:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd rather...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.29,0:12:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no need to take such a reckless gamble.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.61,0:12:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If she'd really survived three years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.31,0:13:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,she'll return to her former self after \Nthe One-Night Bridge appears.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.25,0:13:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no telling when it'll appear... \Nor if it even really exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.35,0:13:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If Hana returns to normal, she has a good marriage offer waiting for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.37,0:13:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't keep the other family waiting any longer!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.51,0:13:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't go along with that...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.42,0:13:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,She's no longer who she once was,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.49,0:13:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,but she's at least still being kept alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.81,0:13:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't treat her like a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.52,0:13:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Ginko-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.63,0:13:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Zen...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.44,0:13:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Already leaving?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.49,0:13:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.88,0:13:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow, I'll have the bridge reinforced with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.82,0:13:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So spend the night at my place.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.39,0:13:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You live here alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.81,0:13:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I've family in the village,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.11,0:14:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'm, you know, ostracized.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.89,0:14:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The people in the village won't\N have anything to do with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.38,0:14:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You didn't think of leaving by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.11,0:14:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I thought of it many times,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.56,0:14:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,but Hana is still alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.13,0:14:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,When Hana's gone, I'll probably leave soon enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.23,0:14:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that noise?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.60,0:14:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.53,0:14:56.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So it finally fell...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.27,0:14:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it because you crossed it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.36,0:15:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,No one's gone across recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.92,0:15:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Well... Rebuild it quickly... please...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.87,0:15:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But we'll have to work on it in our \Nspare time... It'll take a while...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.78,0:15:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Darn... what a bad luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.81,0:15:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Zen!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.73,0:15:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Zen!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.80,0:15:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear you're giving shelter to the mushi-master here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.57,0:15:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He and I still have unfinished business.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.06,0:15:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me a break!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.41,0:15:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That must be a {\i1}tani-modori,{\i0} too...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.25,0:15:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Could there be more of them around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.91,0:16:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hana?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.06,0:16:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter? Where're you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.30,0:16:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Hana...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.85,0:16:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You're warm...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.46,0:16:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You're still very much alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.29,0:16:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You are... Hana, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.90,0:16:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You've just... forgotten everything, that's all, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.58,0:17:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,There she is!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.58,0:17:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Hana...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.58,0:17:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Zen?! What do you think you're doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.09,0:17:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you never to come near Hana again!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.11,0:17:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Hana?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.70,0:17:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,She's not breathing...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.35,0:17:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Hana! Wake up, Hana!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.28,0:17:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Zen! What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.88,0:17:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Hana... is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.11,0:17:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,A black thread... came out from her neck...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.92,0:17:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.25,0:18:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Say Zen, why don't you leave here with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.02,0:18:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be for the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.23,0:18:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.63,0:18:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.31,0:18:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The One-Night Bridge will probably appear tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.09,0:18:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We should be able to cross over it from this side.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.55,0:18:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This area is already filled with {\i1}Nise-kazura{\i0} that gained enough strength to be visible even to your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.10,0:18:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Make up your mind before midnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.62,0:18:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If you miss this chance, there's no telling \Nwhen you might ever leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.49,0:19:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You came... There's no looking back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.91,0:19:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,If you go back on this bridge, you'll fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.91,0:19:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. We'll somehow make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.38,0:19:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yes... he's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.91,0:19:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'll forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.07,0:19:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I know I can forget... once I leave here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.33,0:19:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.52,0:19:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What're you doing? You can no longer go back!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.29,0:19:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't go on... What was once Hana is in here...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.46,0:19:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You're wrong! Hana died three years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.51,0:20:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm not...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.78,0:20:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I kept on going these three years \Nbecause Hana was still alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.78,0:20:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,though it was hard to see her in that state...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.99,0:20:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, when I think about it, \Nit was still better that way...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.93,0:20:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't go forward by stepping on Hana...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.45,0:20:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't go back!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.43,0:21:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I do not know exactly what happened to him after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.05,0:21:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But in all probability...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.61,0:21:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It'll be about another 20 years...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.69,0:21:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...before a one-night bridge spans the ravine again.
